🔗 Proxy Configuration (Vite)

To avoid CORS issues during development:

export default {
  server: {
    proxy: {
      "/api": "http://localhost:3000"
    }
  }
};
✅ Benefit
No need to write full backend URL
Avoids browser CORS blocking
Cleaner API calls
📡 API Integration (Frontend)
useEffect(() => {
  axios.get("/api/jokes")
    .then((res) => setJokes(res.data))
    .catch((err) => console.log(err))
}, []);
🔒 CORS Handling (Backend)

CORS is enabled to allow frontend requests:

import cors from "cors";

app.use(cors());
⚠️ Common Issues & Solutions
❌ CORS Error

Cause: Different origin (port/domain)

Solution:

Enable CORS in backend
Use proxy in frontend
❌ Infinite API Calls

Cause: Missing dependency array in useEffect

useEffect(() => {}, []) // ✅ correct
❌ Axios Import Error
npm install axios
❌ React Rendering Error (Objects not valid)

Fix: Use .map() to render arrays

